Nestlé South Africa is recalling some of the Kit Kat chocolate bars. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Kit Kat lovers will have to take a break. Nestlé South Africa is recalling some of the chocolate bars. The company says that it's possible some of the products may contain pieces of glass. READ: Consumer protection | Implications of product recalls In their statement, Nestlé says it has not yet received any complaints or reported injuries from consumers. Consumers should look out for Kit Kat bars with the following best before dates: 30 September 2022 and 31 October 2022 as well as the Nestlé Kit Kat Mini Bag Milk. The milk producer says the recall is a precautionary measure following quality and safety checks. Nestlé says consumers who may have purchased the products listed above should not consume them but should instead return them for a full refund.